	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For my reference:<br />4th generation consoles: SNES, Genesis, TG16, CDi, Neo Geo<br />5th generation consoles: PlayStation, N64, Jaguar, Saturn, 3DO, PCFX, and a bunch of Japanese exclusives or also-rans I've either not heard of or only heard of in passing (FM Town's Marty, Pioneer's LaserActive, Apple's Pippin, Amiga's CD32, Casio's Loopy, Playdia)<br />6th generation consoles: Dreamcast, PS2, GameCube, Xbox<br /><br />One thing that I'm definitely noticing is that the 5th generation is when <em>everyone</em> came out of the woodwork to try their hand at a new console. Most of the 3d games at the time were really awful, though; IMO the solider games were ones that only lightly used the console's 3d capabilities.<br /><br />In my opinion, the transition from the 1st generation to the 2nd generation, when we finally got interchangeable game paks/cartridges, was so much more important.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


